<DOCNO> AP891208-0008 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
perhaps the ugliest expression 
of the distrust or outright hatred of foreigners here is a leaflet 
dropped on the capital recently by air force planes 
it is directed to the salvadoran patriot and reads you 
have the full and legitimate right to defend your life and 
property if in order to do that you must kill fmln terrorists as 
well as their internationalist allies do it 
fmln stands for the farabundo marti national liberation front 
the guerrilla army waging a 10yearold war for power against a 
succession of usbacked governments 
internationalists are americans canadians europeans and 
nonsalvadoran latin americans who work with the poor either 
through churchaffiliated groups or humanitarian organizations 
several hundred reside in el salvador rightist considers them 
subversives 
the politics of most are quite to the left of center but the 
overwhelming majority work entirely above ground for respected 
organizations such as the lutheran church or the jesuit refugee 
service 
lets destroy them lets finish them off says the flier 
which is signed air force of el salvador below the legend 
with god reason and might we shall conquer 
the air force is the most vehemently rightist of the three 
military branches 
consulted about the incendiary leaflet col rene emilio ponce 
chief of the joint chiefs of staff acknowledged the air force 
wrote it 
he said he interpreted it to refer only to foreigners who are 
active combatants in the insurgent army 
there is no campaign of persecution of foreigners he said 
however more than two dozen internationalists including 10 
americans have been detained during raids on their organizations 
or homes since a rebel offensive began nov 11 
the great majority have been expelled under a state of siege 
imposed in response to the rebel push one american 28yearold 
jennifer casolo of thomaston conn was charged with terrorism 
after police discovered ammunition and explosives buried in her 
back yard 
she denies complicity with the rebels saying the munitions may 
have been buried during one of her frequent trips outside the 
capital 
five spanishborn roman catholic priests were among eight people 
massacred nov 16 rightists had long denounced the five who were 
naturalized salvadorans and their salvadoranborn jesuit 
colleagues as revolutionary ideologues 
the government radio station in the days before the slaying 
broadcast telephone calls from listeners denouncing the priests as 
foreigners and mercenaries of international marxism 
la prensa el salvadors most widely circulated daily newspaper 
dedicated virtually all its editorial page wednesday to two 
articles one titled undesirable foreigners and the other 
headlined stricter controls on entrance 
the long salvadoran conflict has been a stage for the direct 
interference of foreigners who in the most diverse guises from 
simple adventurers to religious missionaries have come to our 
small and convulsed country to experience the drama of the third 
world one editorial said 
many of these noxious characters have dressed themselves in 
the garb of humanitarian piety supposedly accompanying the most 
humble in their pain but in reality giving personal and material 
support to subversion it added 
eileen rosin 35 of long island ny who had worked here for 
two years as the sole representative of medical aid for el 
salvador left hurriedly this week after discovering her office had 
been ransacked 
for eight years medical aid had channeled donated funds for 
prosthetic devices delivered donated medicines to local hospitals 
and sent dozens of children to the united states for operations 
beyond the technical means of salvadoran institutions 
ms rosin whose modest apartment and habits reflected her low 
pay left reluctantly and worried about people her organization was 
supposed to help 
we had two little girls lined up for heart operations in the 
states she said over coffee just before heading for the airport 
i dont know what will happen to them now 
she paused then said but i dont want to rot in jail 
either 
</TEXT>
