three states already have that theres nothing for them to do if 
thats our goal unless we decide that the states have the 
capacity to go down to six and other states will never get below 20 
percent 
see there are a lot of complicated questions like that that 
have to be answered but first we have to get a national goal and 
then well decide how to meet it thats how we got to the moon 
thats how we won world war ii thats how you do things that are 
big 
clinton and south carolina gov carroll campbell jr headed a 
meeting thursday of the national governors association task force 
on education which is preparing national performance goals for 
education as decided at the education summit called by president 
bush in late september 
the task force plans to recommend goals to the governors at 
their winter meeting in february 1990 once goals are approved the 
governors will focus on developing strategies for reaching the 
targets tackling the rest of the agenda set at the summit 
including greater flexibility and enhanced accountability in the 
use of federal resources 
according to clinton the nations educational system will be 
measured by the goals every year beginning in 1991 for a decade 
to determine if learning improves in america 
task force members joined by administration officials heard a 
variety of suggestions from educators advocacy groups and business 
leaders on what those goals should be 
generally the group agreed the nations education system should 
focus on what children actually know as they complete each level of 
schooling rather than on the courses that are being offered 
another key focus the group said should be on making sure 
youngsters enter school healthy and able to learn 
the goals should focus on the ends rather than the means 
said education secretary lauro cavazos we need a handful of 
goals clearly spelled out goals that can lead us in the direction 
of guaranteeing action measuring that action and at the same time 
guaranteeing accountability 
administration officials bristled at one suggestion that all 
high school seniors should be required to pass leaving exams 
with standards set up by what a task force adviser called a 
quasigovernmental institution 
i have not heard from anyone from the governors from 
administration officials since we gave been discussing this for 
several months now the desire or the interest in nationalizing or 
federalizing our education system said roger porter white house 
domestic policy adviser 
however porter did agree educators must more accurately measure 
what students have learned when they leave school 
chester finn a former education department official now at 
vanderbilt university stressed the national goals focus on only 
three areas getting youngsters ready for school preparing 
adolescents for high school and making sure high school students 
are ready for adulthood 
if we can alter the behavior of tens of millions of people as 
a consequence of having these goals then this might be worth 
doing said finn 
nga president terry branstad governor of iowa agreed the list 
of national goals should be short so every school district and 
school can design their own specialized strategies 
