<TEXT>
rabbi davin schoenberger a jewish 
scholar and poet who performed the marriage of anne franks parents 
before fleeing nazi germany has died at age 92 
schoenberger died tuesday at university hospital 
the chief rabbi of aachen germany from 1926 until 1938 
schoenberger married the parents of the jewish teenager who wrote 
a wartime diary read worldwide after she died in a nazi 
concentration camp 
in this country one of schoenbergers poems six million 
jews is widely used in holocaust memorial ceremonies 
schoenberger and his wife were held briefly by the nazis after 
kristallnacht the night of nov 9 1938 when governmentincited 
mobs throughout germany attacked jews and burned and looted 
synagogues and other jewish properties 
he watched his synagogue burn to the ground recalled his 
wife ilse f schoenberger 
the schoenbergers and their young daughter fled europe and 
settled in the united states his chief pulpit was in chicago but 
he later served temple mishkan israel a small congregation in 
selma he had lived in suburban mountain brook since his retirement 
in 1960 
some ministers stay in the study and hit the books all the 
time but my father was a great spiritual counselor said his 
daughter elaine s katz of tuscaloosa 
i had great respect for his scholarship and he was a very 
gentle person and very sensitive to the problems of people said 
rabbi milton grafman rabbi emeritus of temple emanuel where 
schoenberger was a member 
funeral services were scheduled for today at the temple 
schoenberger is survived by his wife daughter and three 
grandchildren 
