senior israeli officials said today that iraqs 
reported launch of longrange missiles capable of carrying 
satellites into space could be dangerous for the region 
the officials who spoke on condition of anonymity expressed 
concern that president saddam husseins regime could use such 
missiles for chemical biological or nuclear warheads 
iraqi radio announced on thursday that a threestage rocket was 
launched tuesday morning from the al anbar space research center 50 
miles west of baghdad it said the missiles had a range of 1240 
miles 
an israeli military source confirmed there was a launching but 
gave no details its true but the implications are not yet 
clear said the source who demanded anonymity 
the us state department said it had heard reports iraq had 
developed intercontinental ballistic missile but knew nothing about 
their validity 
prime minister yitzhak shamirs government issued no formal 
statement but officials said privately that an enhanced iraqi 
missile capability would have a destabilizing effect on the region 
it could lead to a dangerous situation said one official 
adding israel might raise the issue in its diplomatic contacts 
israel is following with concern the development of 
unconventional armament in the arab world in general and in iraq in 
particular the official said iraq has a record of using 
indiscriminately all kinds of unconventional weapons chemical and 
other 
israeli officials refused to reply to questions about whether 
preemptive action might be necessary to forestall development of an 
iraqi missile in june 1981 israeli planes destroyed the osirak 
atomic plant being built near baghdad to prevent hussein from 
developing a nuclear weapons capability 
independent analysts said iraqs launching could trigger a 
missile race in the region but they said baghdad still had a long 
way to go before it could put a spy satellite in space or threaten 
israels technological supremacy 
gerald steinberg a weapons systems expert at hebrew university 
told israel radio that optical systems telemetry and other 
sophisticated systems for a satellite are almost completely 
beyond the iraqi capability now and in the near future 
he said the launching may have been primarily to boost iraqs 
image in which case the military impact would be minimal 
but he said it could mean iraq has developed the ability to 
produce and deploy its own missiles five or 10 years faster than 
expected 
israel launched its own satellite called ofek horizon1 on 
