the southeast coast of africa near madagascar 
a mass rally against denard has been planned for saturday at the 
main mosque in moroni on thursday 1000 youths protested in the 
capital against denard and the mercenaryled presidential guard 
dispersed them with tear gas and clubs 
boni said denards presence would make it difficult for the 
country to hold free elections to choose a new president 
he said south african officials had not negotiated with denard 
about possible exile in south africa but might offer him temporary 
refuge there he said denard owned a home in south africa 
on thursday the mercenaries expelled 11 foreign correspondents 
after seizing their notebooks film and cassette tapes and accusing 
them of inciting antigovernment demonstrations 
they confined the journalists to their hotel in moroni for four 
hours before driving them to the airport for an air france flight 
to nairobi said gary streiker one of the expelled reporters he 
is the nairobibased africa correspondent for the american 
television cable news network 
those expelled thursday included reporters for cnn the reuters 
and agence francepresse news agencies the daily telegraph of 
london radio france internationale and the sygma photo news 
agency said streiker 
denard has not made any public statement on what he is doing or 
why boni said denard told him that if the people demanded he 
should leave he would 
denard has lived in the comoros for 16 years married a local 
woman and adopted the national religion islam he also has 
extensive property holdings 
he has denied reports that he was involved in abdallahs death 
but sources told the associated press that the two men had 
quarreled recently in particular over continued funding of the 
presidential guard which has given denard his power and influence 
in the islands 
denard led a coup in 1975 that ousted abdallah from power 
shortly after the comoran president declared independence from 
france 
in 1978 with the blessing of the french and south african 
government denard led another coup which brought abdallah back to 
power ending the chaotic maoist rule of ali soilij who was shot 
to death 
</TEXT>
