the mood of wall streets stock market 
forecasters is distinctly downbeat as they look ahead to 1990 
thats pretty unusual in an industry known for diehard optimism 
some observers suggest it may be influenced by the depressed state 
of the securities business as much as by the behavior of stock 
prices which still stand near record highs 
