<TEXT>
while ronald reagan was president the 
reigning cliche was that his impact would last far beyond his years 
and that his legacies would be felt in government well into the 
next century 
his time in office was the reagan revolution his fiscal 
ideas were reaganomics his was the reagan era 
but less than a year later the talk about any lingering 
influence is fading and people instead are discussing the 2 
million reagan got for a couple of speeches in japan the sudden 
graying of his hair and the control his wifes astrologer 
exercised over his life in the white house 
many pillars of the reagan program are crumbling even before 
the recent astonishing upheavals in communist east europe reagan 
had retreated from his evil empire characterization of the 
soviet union 
reagans first official act minutes after he took the oath as 
president was to announce an immediate hiring freeze filling a 
campaign promise this begins the process of restoring our 
economic strength and returning the nation to prosperity he said 
he did restore economic strength using enormous amounts of 
borrowed money to fuel the nation longest peacetime economic 
recovery after a deep recession in 198182 that finally subdued 
inflation 
the hiring freeze itself was a failure the executive branch had 
3971802 civilian and military jobs in 1980 at the end of 
reagans eight years that figure had risen to 5079630 
reagans promise to balance the federal budget was hollow jimmy 
carters deficit in 1980 was 738 billion under reagan that 
fattened to 2211 billion in 1986 even as he preached the need 
for restraint in eight years reagan piled up more red ink than 
all 39 previous presidents combined as the debt went from under 1 
trillion to nearly 3 trillion that is one legacy that will 
survive 
his catastrophic illness insurance plan for the elderly which 
the president proclaimed would protect seniors against a choice 
between bankruptcy and death was law for only a year before 
congress repealed it the pressure was applied by prosperous 
seniors who didnt like the feature of which reagan was proudest 
that it was financed by beneficiaries themselves 
reagan proposed the strategic defense initiative star wars 
as the most hopeful possibility of the nuclear age not only 
