<TEXT>
the new york stock exchange has named general 
motors corp chairman roger smith to head a panel examining stock 
market volatility 
the exchange commissioned the panel shortly after a 190point 
drop in the dow jones 30stock industrial average on oct 13 which 
triggered concerns that computerized program trading had damaged 
market stability and driven away individual investors 
i believe addressing investor concerns in todays increasingly 
competitive global financial marketplace is of great importance to 
our nation at this time smith said thursday in a statement 
the equity and related capital markets are a cornerstone of 
the overall health and growth of our countrys marketdriven 
economy and all americans have a vital interest in their 
continuing ability to play that role he said 
the panel is charged with addressing concerns about volatility 
analyzing the impact of rapid price swings in the market and 
recommend changes 
the nyse said the panel also will include representatives of 
individual and institutional investors higher education equities 
and futures exchanges nyse member firms and nyselisted companies 
the exchange said the panels work is expected to take about six 
months 
big board chairman john j phelan jr said smith has a 
longterm perspective on the interests of corporations and their 
shareholders and the importance to the american economy of 
maintaining strong capital markets for all participants 
the stock exchange last month also imposed curbs during periods 
of volatility that limit program trading and give individual 
investors trading priority and asked member firms to refrain from 
program trading during unsteady times 
the reforms followed the oct 13 drop and a sharp 80point rise 
in the dow average on oct 24 
