<DOCNO> AP891208-0248 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
during recent congressional testimony that 
disclosed private pension fund fraud many americans may have felt 
reassured because their nest egg is protected in a socalled 
guaranteed investment contract 
maybe they shouldnt breathe so easily 
those guaranteed contracts often used as part of 401 k 
retirement savings plans are not ironclad the only guarantee 
behind them is the belief that the issuer is of sufficient 
financial strength to keep paying the contracts fixed rate of 
interest 
despite their name chances are no government agency would step 
in to make good should a sponsor of the contracts typically an 
insurance company hit the skids 
many insurance companies put their money in junk bonds risky 
mortgages and other investments that may give an investor pause 
the degree to which they are involved in risky investments is 
reflected in the credit rating they receive from creditrating 
agencies 
most of the companies in this market we have rated aa or 
higher which would suggest that the guarantee is pretty good 
very good actually said weston hicks a vice president at 
moodys investors service inc a creditrating agency that ranks 
companies on a scale of aaa to c 
but he said theres really no protection per se if a 
company issuing a guaranteed investment contract or gic goes 
under 
there has never been a gic default but hicks said there are 
differences in creditworthiness that an investor should consider 
between an insurance company rated aaa and one rated aa or lower 
gics exploded in popularity with the growth of 401 k plans 
which are companysponsored programs that allow employees to put 
away a portion of their income in a savings fund and defer income 
taxes on it until the money is withdrawn at retirement when it is 
taxed at a lower rate 
the 401 k plans have mushroomed as many smaller companies have 
dropped companysponsored pension plans these companies say the 
federal rules that govern pension plans make them too complex and 
costly for small businesses 
employees often have a choice of several investment options for 
their 401 k savings including gics and various stock or bond 
mutual funds many 401 k plans spread the funds among several 
gics thereby reducing the risk to the savings should there be a 
gic default 
the advantages of gics are that they pay a steady rate of 
interest and the principal is fixed with some mutual funds 
principal can deteriorate depending on market conditions while the 
rate of interest is never guaranteed 
gics typically pay interest rates that exceed the yields on 
treasury bills and money market funds by 05 to 15 percentage 
points 
the total amount of money invested in gics exceeds 150 billion 
industry officials estimate 
hank madden an ids securities corp financial planner in 
jacksonville fla said that as tightly regulated as the 
insurance industry is investors should have little to worry 
about with gics 
thus far the insurance industry since the great depression 
has had a pretty good track record of making those guarantees come 
about he said 
even when insurance companies have had financial trouble the 
investors holding annuities and other investments in them have not 
been burnt he said mentioning the bankruptcy reorganization of 
baldwinunited corp several years ago as an example 
however hicks said all is not well in the insurance industry 
today 
theres clearly been a deterioration in the insurance 
industrys credit quality over the past few years he said 
in addition he said the gic market is highly competitive and 
insurance companies are writing this business at quite thin 
spreads in order to make it profitable they have to put a lot of 
liabilities on their books 
</TEXT>
