<TEXT>
oil giant chevron corp said friday it had 
moved to thwart buyout threats raised by pennzoil cos purchase of 
an 88 percent stake suing to force the sale of the stock and 
beefing up its takeover defenses 
chevron in a us district court suit filed late thursday 
scoffed at pennzoils claim that it was not interested in a 
takeover and accused the much smaller company of plotting to force 
a restructuring that would benefit pennzoil 
pennzoil is seeking to put itself in the position to purchase 
additional chevron shares cheaply in the future and to gain an 
advantage in any contest for chevron assets andor in negotiations 
with chevrons management to force an extraordinary 
restructuring the lawsuit read 
chevron stock rose 12 cents to 6612 a share friday on the 
new york stock exchange pennzoil jumped 325 a share to 8650 
pennzoil based in houston disclosed in a securities and 
exchange commission filing thursday that it paid 21 billion to 
buy 315 million chevron shares over the past three months and 
might buy up to another 500 million worth 
the houstonbased company financed the buying spree with a cash 
hoard won in last years settlement of a historic court battle with 
texaco inc pennzoil said in its sec filing and in a statement 
issued friday that its purchases were a longterm investment and 
that it had no interest in taking over chevron 
but chevron the nations fourthlargest oil company in its 
lawsuit accused pennzoil of concealing its true motives and of 
violating federal securities and antitrust laws 
pennzoil has failed to reveal its true intent which is to 
influence chevron management decisions andor force an 
extraordinary restructuring of chevron which would provide 
chevrons assets to pennzoil the suit said 
the suit accused pennzoil of violating both disclosure laws 
applying to potential takeover bidders and a 30day waiting period 
required before making a stock purchase of more than 15 million 
chevron seeks court orders requiring pennzoil to sell the stock 
and prohibiting further purchases without notice 
chevron also wants a declaration that its board acted legally in 
expanding the companys shareholder rights takeover defense the 
company lowered the threshold at which the plan takes effect so it 
would be triggered once an outsider acquired 10 percent or more of 
chevrons outstanding stock instead of 20 percent as before 
chevron also established a new 5 billion bank credit 
arrangement and said all banks involved had agreed not to knowingly 
finance purchases of chevron stock by third parties 
chief us district judge william ingram issued a temporary 
restraining order thursday evening prohibiting pennzoil from suing 
in any other court over the same issues without notifying the san 
francisco court 
pennzoil issued a statement friday saying its chairman j hugh 
liedtke reiterated that pennzoil has acquired its stock position 
in chevron as a longterm investment and that pennzoil has no 
interest in attempting to take over chevron 
chevron said in the suit that pennzoil has stated repeatedly it 
needs to acquire an oil company in order to get favorable tax 
treatment of 3 billion it received from texaco last year the 
money was an outofcourt settlement of a suit pennzoil won over 
texacos 1984 acquisition of getty oil co 
chevron also said the current pennzoil purchases followed the 
same pattern as pennzoils 1988 acquisition of shares in burlington 
resources inc for 380 million pennzoil said those purchases were 
only an investment but sold the stock after burlington filed a 
suit similar to chevrons present suit chevron alleged 
our board believes that pennzoils acquisition of chevron 
shares is disruptive and represents a threat to the realization of 
our longterm business objectives kenneth t derr chevron 
chairman and chief executive said in a news release 
pennzoils disclosure capped months of takeover speculation 
surrounding chevron which attained its present massive size by 
buying gulf corp for 133 billion in 1984 
on wednesday chevron announced a 1 billion sale of 141 
million shares of its common stock to an employee stock ownership 
plan that could make any takeover more difficult the stock about 
5 percent of the companys outstanding shares was added to 11 
percent already held by an employee profitsharing plan 
